/*

SQL - DELETE based on Balance

A table called debtor is created with the following DDL command:

CREATE TABLE debtor (id INT, accountnum INT, name VARCHAR(20), sanctionedamount INT, currentbalance INT);

Write the SQL statement to delete the records of the debtor who have paid off the entire loan amount (i.e., Delete all the debtors who have their currentbalance as 0).


Solution: Done in SQL

*/

DELETE FROM debtor
 WHERE currentbalance=0;